article.title: Explosive Nucleosynthesis in Near-Chandrasekhar Mass White Dwarf Models for Type Ia Supernovae: Dependence on Model Parameters

multiple_choice_question.text: What does the solid line in Figure 1 represent?
What does the dotted line in Figure 2 represent?
choices: Nuclear energy generation rate by carbon detonation
Nuclear energy generation rate by carbon deflagration
Nuclear energy generation rate by NQSE + NSE burning

multiple_choice_question.text: What does a value of [Xi/56Fe] = 0 indicate in Figure 4?
choices: The isotope is not produced in the model.
The isotope is overproduced compared to solar abundances.
The isotope is underproduced compared to solar abundances.
The isotope abundance matches the solar value.

multiple_choice_question.text: Which statement about the effect of central density on nucleosynthesis is supported by Figure 9?
choices: Intermediate mass element (IME) abundances decrease with increasing central density.
Neutron-rich isotope production is suppressed at high central density.
Low-Ye isotopes are significantly enhanced at high central density.
All isotopes show a consistent trend of increasing abundance with increasing central density.
